msgid "Unspecific Redirect URIs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/threat/redirect.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For the <<_oidc-auth-flows,Authorization Code Flow>>, if you register redirect URIs that\n"
"are too general, then it would be possible for a rogue client to impersonate a different client that has a broader scope\n"
"of access.  This could happen for instance if two clients live under the same domain.  So, it's a good idea to make your\n"
"registered redirect URIs as specific as feasible.\n"
